  "prompt": "What do we call video with words on it?",
  "response": "A video that includes words or text overlays is commonly referred to as a **text video** or **caption video**. Here are some more specific terms depending on the context:\n\n1. **Subtitled Video**: If the text is a translation or transcription of the audio.\n2. **Captioned Video**: If the text includes dialogue and sound descriptions, often for accessibility.\n3. **Annotated Video**: If the text provides additional information or commentary.\n4. **Lower Thirds Video**: If the text appears in the lower part of the screen, often used for titles, names, or information.\n5. **Kinetic Typography**: If the text is animated and moves dynamically to emphasize the message.\n\nThese terms can vary based on how the text is used and presented in the video.",
